 <dc:title>A perturbative quantized twist embedded in Minkowski spacetime</dc:title>
 <dc:creator>Strohaber, James</dc:creator>
 <dc:subject>Physics - Optics</dc:subject>
 <dc:description>  In this article, spatially-structured gravitational waves are investigated.
Drawing upon analogies between electrodynamics and general relativity, a new
gauge is found. We investigate the polarization and degrees of freedom of the
resulting radiation. The waves are found to carry orbital angular momentum that
cam be transferred to matter.
